<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1614] single zk node buckling under small node?  connections never timing out?</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1614</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A few (Irfan on the list and jgray) report that a single node zk seems insufficient supporting small cluster &amp;lt; 20 nodes.  This seems odd (though, yeah, we&apos;re recommending serious deploys must have a quorum of &amp;gt;= 3 zk nodes).  Also, reports that all connections fill up and don&apos;t time out though job is done (on IRC).  Take a look.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Check zk stat to see if it&apos;ll dump connections)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12429625">HBASE-1614</key>
            <summary>single zk node buckling under small node?  connections never timing out?</summary>
